From: LineageOS Desktop Project <noreply@local>
Subject: [PATCH] Launcher3: use live taskbar display bounds for placement

Patch summary:
Extend the WindowManager.currentWindowMetrics idiom that the dynamic-display
patch introduced ad-hoc in two spots (Fix 2d's getCurrentDisplaySize and
Fix 2f's setTaskbarWindowSize) into a reusable
TaskbarActivityContext.getLiveDisplayBounds(), and route the rest of the
taskbar's placement / clamping / touch-region / bubble code paths through it.
Dynamic desktop displays can resize without DeviceProfile being a perfect
source of live window truth — keep DeviceProfile for intended layout sizes
(icon grid, font scale, etc.), but for runtime placement decisions on
dynamic desktop displays, prefer live window bounds so resize lag does not
mis-place popups, overlay windows, the all-apps view, bottom-edge swipe
regions, or bubbles. The PopupContainerWithArrow.getCurrentDisplaySize hunk
in dynamic-display.patch is replaced here with a call through the new getter;
the WindowManager import added there is no longer needed and is removed.

Also keep bubbles aligned with the taskbar when the taskbar is forced to stay
at the screen edge on desktop/freeform displays. Without this, Launcher can be
in NORMAL/HOME while desktop tasks are still visible, so the bubble stash
controller chooses the home/hotseat Y target and lifts the bubble bar under
the expanded bubble window instead of leaving it on the taskbar.

Applies on top of packages-apps-Launcher3-dynamic-display.patch (whose
WindowManager-based helpers this patch generalizes) and
packages-apps-Launcher3-taskbar-deep-shortcuts.patch.

